Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.02,0:01:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0008,,{\blur3}宇宙:多大 多远 多快{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.82,0:26:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0008,,{\an8\blur3}咨询《宇宙》团队{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.29,0:00:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}上溯至宇宙初始 周遭还只是一片漆黑{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In the beginning, there was darkness.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.62,0:00:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不知何时 忽地一声巨响{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And then... Bang!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.69,0:00:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}时间空间以及物质皆由此发端{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Giving birth to an endless expanding existence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.49,0:00:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}此后不断膨胀 延伸 永无止境{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of time, space, and matter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.02,0:00:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一天 新的发现都在不断为我们解开{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Every day, new discoveries are unlocking{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.48,0:00:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}蕴藏于这里的那些神秘莫测{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the mysterious, the mind-blowing,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.60,0:00:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}令人大开眼界 致命的秘密{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the deadly secrets of a place we call{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.61,0:00:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们称这个地方为"宇宙"{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the universe.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.37,0:00:26.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}宇宙的数字让人类智力感到惊恐{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The numbers of the universe boggle the human mind.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.70,0:00:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在可观察到的那部分宇宙里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In the observable part of the universe,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.83,0:00:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有无数的物体 比如1 000亿个星系{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}there is something like 100 billion galaxies{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.48,0:00:34.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}而每一个星系有数十亿的恒星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Each with billions of stars.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.63,0:00:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}仙女座星系大约距离我们250万光年{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The Andromeda galaxy is about 2.5 million light-years away.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.87,0:00:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}地球围绕太阳运行的速度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The Earth is orbiting the Sun{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.79,0:00:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}约为66 000英里/小时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}at a speed of about 66,000 miles per hour.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.46,0:00:50.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}要去理解如此巨大的尺寸 距离和速度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Most of us give up even trying to comprehend such titanic sizes,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.09,0:00:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们大多数人会举手投降{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}distances, and speeds.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.77,0:00:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有办法能把宇宙的一部分请到地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But are there ways to bring the sweep of the cosmos down to Earth{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.30,0:01:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}帮助我们去了解它{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to help us understand{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.17,0:01:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有多大 多远和多快吗？{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to help us understand how big, how far, and how fast?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.63,0:01:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}行星地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Planet Earth{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.88,0:01:23.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}把它所有的辽阔土地 深深海洋和崇山峻岭{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}For all its wide expanses, deep seas,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.12,0:01:25.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}都加起来{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and massive mountains{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.49,0:01:28.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}也不过是一颗小尘埃{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Amounts to a speck of dust{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.64,0:01:32.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}如果与广袤的宇宙相比较的话{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}when stacked up against the immensity of the cosmos.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.85,0:01:36.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}宇宙可观察得到的部分{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The observable universe contains on{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.94,0:01:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}包含大约1 000亿个星系{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the order of 100 billion galaxies.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.30,0:01:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}而每一个星系 比如银河 包含着大约1 000亿颗恒星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And then each galaxy, like the Milky Way, contains on the order of 100 billion stars.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.70,0:01:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}数字快速攀升到百万级 十亿级{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The numbers quickly get up into the millions and then the billions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.89,0:01:52.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}甚至达到万亿级{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and even the trillions.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.58,0:01:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们完全丧失了感觉 不知道它的意义{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And by then, we've really lost all sense of what that really means.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.81,0:02:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}人类的智力适宜于处理{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The human mind is finely tuned{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.18,0:02:03.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}日常生活中遇到的规模{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to deal with the scale of day-to-day experience.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.50,0:02:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}大脑能明白一天50英里的旅行{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The brain can understand traveling 50 miles in a day.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.62,0:02:11.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但500 000英里呢？{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But what about 500,000?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.67,0:02:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有人也许知道{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And a person may know what it's{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.05,0:02:15.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}每小时100英里移动是怎样的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And a person may know what it's like to move at 100 miles per hour.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.53,0:02:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但每小时1亿英里呢？{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But what about 100 million?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.45,0:02:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}数字达到百万 十亿和万亿级别时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Numbers like millions and billions, and certainly trillions,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.97,0:02:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}对大多数人来说 很难以想象了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}are very hard for most people to imagine,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.63,0:02:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因为 平心而论 大多数人{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}because, frankly, most of us{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.30,0:02:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}没有十亿或万亿的东西{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}don't have billions or trillions of anything.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.09,0:02:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以 如果大脑不能理解宇宙级的规模{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So how can we ever know the universe{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.86,0:02:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们怎样才能去了解宇宙它呢？{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}if our brains can't really comprehend its massive scale?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.21,0:02:46.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}对宇宙物体建立比例模型 能帮上这个忙{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Doing scale models of objects in the universe is really helpful,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.75,0:02:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因为这样能把它们按比例缩小到{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}because it brings them down to sizes{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.63,0:02:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们能想像的大小 日常生活里见到的大小{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that we can imagine, that we do see in our normal, everyday lives.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.27,0:02:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们首先把夜空中的那些大牌主角{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We can start by cutting the biggest players of the night sky{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.70,0:03:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}行星 恒星和星系{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Planets, stars and galaxies{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.01,0:03:05.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}按地球物体的比例缩小{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Down to an earthly scale.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.27,0:03:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有两种方式去形容大小{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}There are two ways to evaluate size.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.76,0:03:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们可以测量其尺寸-- 高度 长度和宽度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We can measure dimensions--Meaning height, length and width{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.76,0:03:18.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}或者计算它的体积 也就是质量{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}or calculate bulk, also known as mass.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.77,0:03:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但大体积不总是意味着大质量{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Bigger doesn't always mean more massive.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.25,0:03:27.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}比方说 一个气球与保龄球体积相同{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Let's say a balloon has the same volume as a bowling ball.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.01,0:03:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但保龄球更重 因为它密度大{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But the bowling ball has more mass, because it's denser...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.21,0:03:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它把更多的质量塞进同样的体积里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's just got more mass crammed into that same volume.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.70,0:03:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}为帮助我们理解宇宙里的一些超级大家伙{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}To help get a grasp on some of the immense masses floating around our universe,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.85,0:03:48.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}天文学家劳拉.丹丽参观了一场怪兽车比赛{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}astronomer Laura Danly visits a monster truck rally...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.07,0:03:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那里经常有质量非常悬殊的物体相互碰撞{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}A place where objects of hugely differing masses often collide.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.93,0:04:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}从小玩具车到特大怪兽车 我们无所不有{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We' got everything from a small toy truck to the giant monster truck...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.54,0:04:07.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}一系列的不同质量{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And that gives us a range of mass{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.24,0:04:08.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}将帮助我们去了解{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that will help us understand{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.62,0:04:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太阳系里的物体互比质量会如何{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}how massive things are in our Solar System compared to each other,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.49,0:04:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太阳与其它恒星比较质量又如何{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and how massive our own Sun is compared to some other stars.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.94,0:04:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们从木星开始比较{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We begin the comparison with Jupiter,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.57,0:04:24.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它理所当然地被认为是行星之王{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}known as the king of planets, and for good reason.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.00,0:04:28.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因为它的质量超过了4 000亿亿亿磅{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Its mass amounts to more than 4 octillion pounds...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.47,0:04:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}也就是说 数字4后面跟着27个零{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}That's a four followed by 27 zeros.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.88,0:04:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}换而言之 超过300个地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Put another way, it would take more than 300 Earths{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.28,0:04:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}才能相当于木星的质量{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to match Jupiter's mass.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.57,0:04:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但即便如此 它与太阳相比还是微不足道{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But even that is measly when compared to the Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.98,0:04:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太阳是我们太阳系里迄今为止最重的事物{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The Sun is by far the most massive thing in our Solar System.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.04,0:04:54.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}木星是最大的行星 但它比木星重1 000倍{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's about 1,000 times more massive than Jupiter, the biggest planet.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.53,0:04:58.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}相比之下 在我后面的这辆车大约3 000磅{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Well, by comparison, this car behind me is about 3,000 pounds,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.01,0:05:02.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}而这架小玩具卡车大约3磅{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and this little toy truck is about 3 pounds.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.52,0:05:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以 它们的差异与太阳和木星的差异相当{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So that's about the same difference between the Sun and Jupiter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.95,0:05:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这是一边倒的差异 3 000磅很好地说明了问题{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's a crushing difference, as 3,000 pounds make perfectly clear.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.70,0:05:22.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但要记住 这是怪兽车比赛{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But remember, this is a monster truck rally,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.84,0:05:26.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}代表我们太阳的这辆烂车{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and the junk car representing our Sun{\r}
