Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.95,0:21:20.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}开始{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Let's do it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.31,0:21:24.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在这个按比例缩小的太阳系里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Each foot in this scaled-down Solar System{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.01,0:21:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}每英尺代表着行星之间100万英里的距离{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}represents 1 million miles in the distances between the planets.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.90,0:21:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们到了水星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And here we are at Mercury.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.44,0:21:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}36英尺{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And that's 36 feet.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.61,0:21:40.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在实际当中 它距离太阳是360万英里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In reality, it's actually about 36 million miles away from the Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.04,0:21:48.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在太阳系里 第一个行星与太阳距离有多远{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's amazing just how far the very first planet{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.11,0:21:49.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}让人惊异{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of the Solar System is from the Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.00,0:21:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}现在 我们向第二个行星进发{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So now let's go on to the second planet.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.13,0:21:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}好{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Yeah.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.90,0:22:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们到金星了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So here we are at Venus.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.72,0:22:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}距离是67英尺{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And that's 67 feet.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.51,0:22:08.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因此 这个小不点代表着金星到太阳的距离{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So this bead representing Venus is about twice as far{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.94,0:22:11.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是水星的两倍{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}from the Sun as Mercury is.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.71,0:22:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}事实上的距离 则是670万英里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's actually, in reality, about 67 million miles away.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.84,0:22:21.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们到地球了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And here we are at the Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.60,0:22:23.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}93英尺{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And that's 93 feet.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.15,0:22:27.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这个弹珠在这里代表着地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We have the Earth here represented by this marble.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.15,0:22:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它实际上距离太阳930万英里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And, in fact, it's in reality 93 million miles away from the Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.64,0:22:37.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}从这里见到的保龄球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The way the bowling ball looks, in terms of the size,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.31,0:22:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}与我们天空里的太阳{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}from here, is about the size{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.66,0:22:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}大小很接近{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the sun appears in our sky.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.89,0:22:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}蓝色珠子代表地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We have this blue bead representing the Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.38,0:22:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}而在大约2.5英寸之外 有一颗小得多的珠子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And about 2 1/2 inches away, we have a much smaller bead{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.65,0:22:51.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它代表着月亮{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}representing the Moon.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.72,0:22:53.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}还记得比例不一样时的情形吧{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Remember that on a different scale,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.89,0:22:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}当地球如同篮球大小时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}with Earth the size of a basketball,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.76,0:22:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}月亮是在21英尺之外{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the Moon was 21 feet away.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.30,0:23:01.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}为了让整个太阳系都出现在画面里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}To bring the whole Solar System into the picture,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.36,0:23:06.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们只能把地月距离按比例缩小到几英寸{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we've had to scale down the Earth-Moon distance to mere inches.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.26,0:23:09.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}眼前这微小的地月距离{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}This tiny distance between the Earth and Moon{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.97,0:23:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是迄今为止载人太空探险的极限{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is the limit so far of manned exploration of space.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.62,0:23:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}希望我们在未来日子里做得更多和更好{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Hopefully, we'll do a lot better in the years to come.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.34,0:23:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在我们跑道上 火星运行在地球之外49英尺的地方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}On our runway, Mars orbits another 49 feet away,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.36,0:23:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}即距离太阳大约1 420万英里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}or almost 142 million miles from the Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.38,0:23:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在火星之外 这次的距离就非常非常远了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The distances beyond Mars are about to get much, much larger.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.40,0:23:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们到了木星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Here we are... Jupiter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.01,0:23:45.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}现在离太阳是484英尺{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We're at 484 feet from the Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.24,0:23:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是火星到太阳距离的三倍{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}That's actually three times as far from the Sun as Mars is.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.06,0:23:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}神奇的是 这个距离里的所有小不点{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}With all this space between these tiny marbles,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.76,0:23:58.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就是我们从地球用肉眼能看到的行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it's a wonder we can see the planets from Earth at all.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.61,0:24:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它说明了太阳极为明亮{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It tells us that the Sun is incredibly bright...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.39,0:24:07.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以阳光能照射到这些天体 并被它们反射回地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So that the light from the Sun can go out to these bodies, reflect off them,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.56,0:24:10.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因此我们能用肉眼看到它们{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and then come back to here on Earth for us to see them.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.45,0:24:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}好了 向外面的土星前进{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Okay, onwards and outwards to Saturn.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.53,0:24:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}好 出发{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}All right, here we go.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.22,0:24:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们这两位太空探险者发现 土星距离太阳886英尺{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Our two space explorers find Saturn 886 feet from the Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.38,0:24:29.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在现实当中 土星距离太阳8 860英里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In fact, Saturn, at 886 million miles away from the Sun,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.09,0:24:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}差不多是木星到太阳距离的两倍{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is almost twice the distance from the Sun that Jupiter is from the Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.98,0:24:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以说 我们走得相当远了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So we've come a huge extra distance{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.01,0:24:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}不过 还没有走完整个太阳系{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and we're not even done with the Solar System yet.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.05,0:24:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在1 800英尺的地方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}At 1,800 feet, the scaled orbit of Uranus stands{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.37,0:24:47.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}矗立着按比例缩小的天王星 它比土星远两倍{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the scaled orbit of Uranus stands twice as far as Saturn...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.40,0:24:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}即距离太阳18亿英里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}1.8 billion miles from the Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.77,0:24:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我难以看清后面的太阳{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}I can hardly see the Sun back there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.65,0:25:00.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}同时几乎看不到我们的下一站{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And I can actually hardly see Neptune in the distance,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.18,0:25:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}位于远处的海王星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}which is our next stop on our journey.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.68,0:25:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}走吧？{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Shall we go?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.44,0:25:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}走{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Let's go.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.05,0:25:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}天哪 好远{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Jeez, that's far.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.17,0:25:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是啊{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Yep.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.33,0:25:19.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们到了最后一个行星--海王星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And here we are... Neptune... the last of the planets.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.05,0:25:23.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}距离太阳是2 798英尺{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}2,798 feet from our Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.40,0:25:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这个结果换算为现实世界里的距离时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}That from our model translates into the real-world distance{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.79,0:25:31.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}从海王星到太阳 距离大约是30亿英里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of almost 3 billion miles that Neptune is away from the Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.11,0:25:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}距离越远 恒星要花越长的时间去环绕太阳一周{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}This far out, a planet takes a long time to do an orbit around the Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.40,0:25:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}海王星上的一年 大约是165个地球年{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The neptunian year is about 165 of our Earth years.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.01,0:25:46.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}说起来 我们是在一个海王星年之前{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In fact, only one of those neptunian years has passed since{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.78,0:25:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}才发现了海王星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Neptune was actually discovered.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.23,0:25:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}通过这次测量{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Viewed on this scale,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.10,0:25:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}让人惊奇的是太阳万有引力的影响无处不在{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it's a wonder the Sun's gravity has any effect at all.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.89,0:26:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}甚至还影响到太阳系里在海王星之外的天体{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And there's still more to the Solar System beyond Neptune...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.55,0:26:05.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}包括较小的天体 比如冥王星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Including smaller bodies, like Pluto...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.48,0:26:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}以及差不多距离1光年远的黑暗寒冷的彗星群{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And then, nearly a light-year away, clouds of dark icy comets.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.33,0:26:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}如果说我们太阳系里行星的间距{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}If the space between the planets in our Solar System{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.18,0:26:20.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}让人类的理解感到吃力{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}strains human comprehension,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.26,0:26:24.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那么恒星之间和星系之间的巨大间距{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}then the vast distances between stars and galaxies{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.21,0:26:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就会把它压垮{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}totally overwhelms it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.84,0:26:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}天文学家怎么知道恒星有多远{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}That astronomers even know how far away stars are{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.41,0:26:35.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}纽约布鲁克林的诺拉对此觉得迷惑不解{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is a mystery to Nora from Brooklyn, New York,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.44,0:26:37.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}她想…{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}who wants to...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.32,0:26:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}"我们怎样测量恒星间和星系间的距离？"{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}How do we measure the distance to stars and galaxies?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.18,0:26:47.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}诺拉 这问题非常复杂{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Nora, that's actually a pretty complex question.{\r}
